        "32be1fd9-b092-4e4d-a2bf-20f6e530f797": {
            "category": "PythonApp",
            "categoryType": "Application",
            "id": "32be1fd9-b092-4e4d-a2bf-20f6e530f797",
            "name": "RASCIL_ predict_awprojection",
            "description": "predict_awprojection\npredict_awprojection(vis: rascil.data_models.memory_data_models.BlockVisibility, model: rascil.data_models.memory_data_models.Image, gcfcf=None, **kwargs)\u2192 rascil.data_models.memory_data_models.BlockVisibility[source]\uf0c1\nPredict using convolutional degridding and an AW kernel\n\nNote that the gridding correction function (gcf) and convolution function (cf) can be passed as a partial function. So the caller must supply a partial function to calculate the gcf, cf tuple for an image model.\n\nParameters\nvis \u2013 blockvisibility to be predicted\n\nmodel \u2013 model image\n\nReturns\nresulting visibility (in place works)",
            "x": 1100.0593447443716,
            "y": 451.18722594743934,
            "repositoryUrl": "",
            "commitHash": "",
            "paletteDownloadUrl": "",
