        "814b520e-c72b-4007-b424-58bc4485193f": {
            "category": "PythonApp",
            "categoryType": "Application",
            "id": "814b520e-c72b-4007-b424-58bc4485193f",
            "name": "RASCIL_apply_gaintable",
            "description": "apply_gaintable(vis: rascil.data_models.memory_data_models.BlockVisibility, gt: rascil.data_models.memory_data_models.GainTable, inverse=False, **kwargs)\u2192 rascil.data_models.memory_data_models.BlockVisibility[source]\uf0c1\nApply a gain table to a block visibility\n\nThe corrected visibility is:\n\nV_corrected = {g_i * g_j^*}^-1 V_obs\nIf the visibility data are polarised e.g. polarisation_frame(\u201clinear\u201d) then the inverse operator represents an actual inverse of the gains.\n\nParameters\nvis \u2013 blockvisibility to have gains applied\n\ngt \u2013 Gaintable to be applied\n\ninverse \u2013 Apply the inverse (default=False)\n\nReturns: input vis with gains applied",
            "x": 1697.3597635764597,
            "y": 439.8313082799201,
            "repositoryUrl": "",
            "commitHash": "",
            "paletteDownloadUrl": "",
            "dataHash": "",
            "parentId": "36352250-de8e-4a38-a6d3-94b123a0d9de",
